  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are some Indian Fast-fashion Brands?",
  "response": "India has seen a significant rise in fast-fashion brands that cater to the growing demand for trendy and affordable clothing. Here are some popular Indian fast-fashion brands:\n\n1. **Zara (with an Indian presence)**\n   - Zara, although a global brand, has a strong presence in India and is known for its fast-fashion offerings.\n\n2. **H&M (with an Indian presence)**\n   - H&M is another international brand that has gained popularity in India for its affordable and trendy clothes.\n\n3. **Forever 21 (with an Indian presence)**\n   - Forever 21, an American brand, has stores in India and is well-known for its fast-fashion appeal.\n\n4. **Max Fashion**\n   - Max Fashion is an Indian brand that offers a wide range of affordable clothing for men, women, and children.\n\n5. **Pantaloons**\n   - Pantaloons, owned by Aditya Birla Fashion and Retail, is a popular choice for trendy and budget-friendly fashion.\n\n6. **Westside**\n   - Westside, part of the Tata Group, offers a variety of fashionable clothing at reasonable prices.\n\n7. **FBB (Fashion at Big Bazaar)**\n   - FBB is a popular choice for budget-conscious shoppers looking for the latest trends.\n\n8. **Vero Moda**\n   - While originally a Danish brand, Vero Moda has a significant presence in India and is known for its fast-fashion offerings.\n\n9. **ONLY**\n   - ONLY, another brand by the Bestseller group, is popular among young Indian women for its trendy clothes.\n\n10. **Biba**\n    - Biba is an Indian brand known for its fusion wear that combines traditional and modern styles at affordable prices.\n\nThese brands have established themselves in the Indian market by offering fashionable clothing that is accessible and affordable to a wide audience.",
